titleStmt.title: An elegy humbly offered to the memory of the Reverend Father in God Doctor Humphry Henchman, late Bishop of London, who departed this life the 8th of October 1675.

notesStmt.note: Verse: "Stand off, you Common Vouchers for the Dead ..."
Within mourning border, with emblems and motto at head.
Reproduction of original in the British Library.
